# PyInstaller
#  Usually these files are written by a python script, and contain the binrary number of lines of code from the Python source that were used to generate the distribution.
#  This file is often included in the source distribution, but it's not strictly necessary. 
#  It's usually a good idea to include it in the source distribution, so that the users can rebuild the project.
#  However, if you're using a version control system, you might want to exclude it.
#  Alternatively, you can include it in the source distribution but exclude it from the version control system.
#  It's up to you.
#  In this case, we'll exclude it.
*.manifest
*.spec

# Installer logs
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

